dataObjects.title: Biology
dataObjects.description: Adults feed on worms, crustaceans, insects and plant matter (Ref. 7020).  Oviparous (Ref. 205).  Distinct pairs breed on densely grown weedy places (Ref. 205).

dataObjects.description: South America:  Amazon and Orinoco River basins (Ref. 36801).  Reported from Suriname (Ref. 59052).
